data.text:
So disappointing.
I had booked in advance for a party of 6.
When we arrived on Saturday evening, we discovered the only option was carvery.  The staff said they had phoned me earlier in the day and left a message, but the only missed call I had was from "Wacky Warehouse", which I assumed was spam as I had nothing to do with Wacky Warehouse (not realising that they are at the same venue) and so did not answer.  I do not have voicemail activated on my account.
Anyway, we decided carvery would be fine for us all.
In the end, we discovered the process for getting our carvery through trial and error, as the staff gave us no information.
There were no Yorkshire puddings available - when we asked, we were shown a tray of burnt puddings on a shelf as if that explained it...  The peas were so bad that most of our party left them on the plate.
Saving graces were that the meat was tasty and the roast potatoes surprisingly ok.
By 8.20, staff were clearly packing away and all ready to close the restaurant and we felt uncomfortable staying any longer so did not attempt to get any dessert (which we presumed would be unavilable anyway) and headed off to somewhere more welcoming for our coffees.
We won't be returning...

Very Happy. Excellent service.

My son and his carer come here. We are relatively new customers and I’m so happy with the food and service, that I will be making sure my son comes here for his healthy hearty lunch to carry him through his busy afternoon of play.

Lisa has been especially nice and welcoming. She is extremely patient on the phone and really helpful answering any questions even though you can hear how busy it is in the background she has been very nice and explaining things and not in a rushed or impatient way as to get you off the phone. So thank you for this Lisa it makes the world of difference to know that your needs are cared for.

My son has additional and complex needs and this place has very good experience with young people and adults whom I believe return there on a regular basis and I believe they always try to cater for this as far as trying to make sure that you have your same seating each week. Although I do understand that ...if you don’t book ...this might not always be possible as other people will be dining too.

I have been sent photos of my son tucking into his hearty food with beautiful looking vegetables and even down to the sauce included dishes have been served on a separate dish! This is 5*****s for me because to know how important this can be to somebody with additional needs means so much to my heart to know how important that is and to put this into place just means the world to me that our children’s and adults needs are really taken care of and that they understand and more to the point “care” So huge thank you for this everyone xx

There is also a slush machine that works very well as a “special surprise/treat/reward” or bribe lol for good behaviour 😉

We will be a regular from now even though we live miles away, you can’t beat the service and friendliness and good food that you get here 😁

Brilliant well done and keep up the fabulous work xx

Its the 2nd year running now that my family and i have had our xmas dinner here (all 13 of us).
I will certainly be returning next year also.
The standard of food was very high and the customer service amazing.
All the staff couldnt have been anymore helpful.
Whats really nice to see is the respect the manager has for her staff also.
Richard Bransons famous words "train your staff well so they will want to leave, treat them well and they will stay"
This is certainly reflected in the whole dinning experience.
I would also like to mention that the wilmslow branch of faye and square is certainly the best faye and square dinning i have experience with regards to good quality food at affordable prices (very realistic) also the courtesy of staff.
I do tend to use this faye and square as a benchmark for all the other faye and squares and am dubious going to another as in my experience dont compare. Gold standard, i do eat out alot and will certainly praise any restaurant where praise is due and will also critique somewhere if i am not happy.
So well done to all the staff at this facility im sure the manager/land lady is very proud.
Happy xmas and thank you for making our day that bit more special once again.
Really appreciated customers and thanks for our xmas card that was a lovely touch.
